    "description": "A database of organ-specific metastasis induced by human cancer cell lines in mouse models.\n\nThe organotropism is the propensity of metastatic cancer cells to colonize preferably certain distant organs, resulting in a non-random distribution of metastases. In order to shed light on this behaviour, several studies were performed by the injection of human cancer cell lines into immunocompromised mouse models.",
